text: Azikeyevo () is a rural locality (a village) in Bolsheustyikinsky Selsoviet, Mechetlinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 684 as of 2010. There are 15 streets. == Geography == It is located 10 km from Bolsheustyikinskoye. == References == Category:Rural localities in Mechetlinsky District
title: Azikeyevo, Mechetlinsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
